{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772181458285,"sessionID":"ses_361c37f15ffeuVWV0XN4ZPvLel","part":{"id":"prt_c9e3f0bf20022IEBHMKRW4PBco","sessionID":"ses_361c37f15ffeuVWV0XN4ZPvLel","messageID":"msg_c9e3f084b00161Ut70pPiLCBgN","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_01QbMGHEM2S2yB4Big49avu8","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/spec/behavior/state-model.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/spec/behavior/state-model.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: # State Model\n2: \n3: > Key state entities, their fields, transitions, and the modules that own them.\n4: \n5: **Source examined at commit:** `ecc95c0` (2026-02-27)\n6: \n7: ## Overview\n8: \n9: State in super-ralph is partitioned across three scopes:\n10: \n11: - **In-process transient state** — lives only for the duration of a single\n12:   `runPhaseLoop` call and is discarded when the process exits.\n13: - **On-disk persistent state** — written to the `.super-ralph/` directory\n14:   and survives process restarts.\n15: - **External state** — owned by out-of-process services (the opencode server\n16:   and the `br` CLI); super-ralph reads and mutates it only through typed\n17:   interfaces.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## In-Process Transient State\n22: \n23: ### SessionState (run counters)\n24: \n25: Defined in `src/run-state.ts:13`. A private interface maintained by the\n26: `RunTracker` instance returned from `startRunTracker`. Its fields are:\n27: \n28: | Field | Type | Initial value | Description |\n29: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n30: | `runId` | `string` | set at construction | Unique run identifier |\n31: | `status` | `\"running\" \\| \"completed\" \\| \"failed\"` | `\"running\"` | Current run lifecycle status |\n32: | `description` | `string` | from `setup()` return | Human-readable phase description |\n33: | `maxIterations` | `number` | from `setup()` return | Upper bound on iterations |\n34: | `startedAt` | ISO 8601 string | construction time | When the run was created |\n35: | `updatedAt` | ISO 8601 string | updated on each write | Timestamp of last state flush |\n36: | `currentIteration` | `number` | `0` | Index of the iteration currently executing |\n37: | `completed` | `number` | `0` | Count of successfully completed iterations |\n38: | `failed` | `number` | `0` | Count of failed or error-status iterations |\n39: | `skipped` | `number` | `0` | Count of blocked or skipped iterations |\n40: \n41: **Mutations:** `updateFromEvent` (`src/run-state.ts:72`) maps incoming\n42: `EngineEvent` types to counter increments:\n43: \n44: - `iteration.started` → sets `currentIteration`\n45: - `iteration.completed` → increments `completed`\n46: - `iteration.blocked` → increments `skipped`\n47: - `iteration.failed`, `iteration.error` → increments `failed`\n48: - `loop.completed` → overwrites `completed`, `failed`, `skipped` with final\n49:   loop totals\n50: \n51: **Status transitions:**\n52: \n53: ```text\n54: \"running\"\n55:    |\n56:    +-- finalize(\"completed\")  →  \"completed\"   (when failed == 0)\n57:    |\n58:    +-- finalize(\"failed\")     →  \"failed\"      (when failed > 0 or\n59:                                                 exception in loop)\n60: ```\n61: \n62: `finalize` is called exactly once: in the engine's `finally` block\n63: (`src/engine.ts:251`) or at the end of a successful loop\n64: (`src/engine.ts:244`).\n65: \n66: ### Engine Loop Counters\n67: \n68: Declared in `src/engine.ts:88–93` as plain `let`/`const` bindings:\n69: \n70: | Binding | Type | Description |\n71: | --- | --- | --- |\n72: | `iteration` | `number` | Current 1-based loop counter; decremented on retry |\n73: | `completed` | `number` | Iterations that resolved `\"complete\"` or `\"phase_done\"` |\n74: | `failed` | `number` | Iterations that resolved as any failure status |\n75: | `skipped` | `number` | Iterations that resolved `\"blocked\"` |\n76: | `retryCount` | `Map<string, number>` | Retry attempts keyed by `iterationLabel` |\n77: | `startTime` | `number` | `Date.now()` at loop entry; used to compute `totalTime` |\n78: \n79: **Retry bookkeeping:** When the failure strategy is `\"retry\"` and\n80: `retryCount.get(label) < max_retries`, `iteration` is decremented by one\n81: (`src/engine.ts:183`) so the same item is selected again on the next loop\n82: turn. The `retryCount` map is never reset within a run; retries accumulate\n83: across the entire run, not per-phase-invocation. [CONFIRMED: `src/engine.ts`]\n84: \n85: ### IterationResult (per-iteration record)\n86: \n87: Defined in `src/types.ts:48`. Built at the end of each iteration and pushed\n88: to the `iterations` array:\n89: \n90: | Field | Type | Description |\n91: | --- | --- | --- |\n92: | `iteration` | `number` | 1-based iteration index |\n93: | `beadId` | `string` | bead ID or `\"iter-<N>\"` if no bead |\n94: | `beadTitle` | `string` | Human-readable iteration label |\n95: | `status` | see below | Outcome classification |\n96: | `reason` | `string \\| undefined` | Agent-provided explanation |\n97: | `model` | `string` | `\"provider/model\"` string used |\n98: | `duration` | `number` | Wall-clock milliseconds |\n99: | `cost` | `number \\| undefined` | Reported session cost |\n100: | `tokens` | object \\| undefined | `{ input, output, reasoning }` counts |\n101: | `filesChanged` | `string[] \\| undefined` | Paths modified in the session |\n102: | `transcriptPath` | `string \\| undefined` | Relative path to transcript log |\n103: \n104: **Status values** (`src/types.ts:52`):\n105: \n106: | Value | Meaning |\n107: | --- | --- |\n108: | `\"complete\"` | Agent signalled task done; loop continues |\n109: | `\"phase_done\"` | Agent signalled all work done; loop exits |\n110: | `\"blocked\"` | bead has unresolved dependencies; skipped |\n111: | `\"failed\"` | Agent explicitly reported failure |\n112: | `\"stalled\"` | Agent stopped producing output [INFERRED: stall detection] |\n113: | `\"timeout\"` | Wall-clock deadline exceeded |\n114: | `\"error\"` | Exception thrown inside iteration try-block |\n115: \n116: ### StreamCapture (session output buffer)\n117: \n118: Defined in `src/output-parser.ts`. Holds two accumulation fields:\n119: \n120: | Field | Max size | Description |\n121: | --- | --- | --- |\n122: | `raw` | 250,000 characters | Raw SSE event lines from the session |\n123: | `display` | 250,000 characters | Rendered display text for the operator |\n124: \n125: Both buffers are capped at 250,000 characters. [CONFIRMED: `src/output-parser.ts`]\n126: Buffers are discarded when the session completes and the `PromptResult` is\n127: returned to the engine.\n128: \n129: ### ServerHandle\n130: \n131: Returned by `startServer()` or `connectToServer()` in `src/opencode.ts`.\n132: Holds a reference to the active opencode server client and URL for the\n133: duration of a run. Closed by `server.close()` in the engine's cleanup\n134: function (`src/engine.ts:38`).\n135: \n136: ---\n137: \n138: ## On-Disk Persistent State\n139: \n140: All persistent state lives under `<project-root>/.super-ralph/`.\n141: \n142: ### session.json (global latest-run pointer)\n143: \n144: **Path:** `.super-ralph/session.json`\n145: **Written by:** `src/run-state.ts:writeState` on every `recordEvent` call\n146: and on `finalize`.\n147: **Read by:** Not read by any module; intended for operator inspection.\n148: **Format:** JSON serialization of `SessionState` with two-space indentation.\n149: \n150: This file is overwritten (not appended) on every state change and always\n151: reflects the most recently active run. It serves as a live mirror of\n152: `SessionState` for external tooling and operators.\n153: \n154: ### runs/`<runId>`/session.json (per-run state)\n155: \n156: **Path:** `.super-ralph/runs/<runId>/session.json`\n157: **Written by:** Same as above — every `recordEvent` and `finalize`.\n158: **Read by:** `src/run-status.ts:getRunStatus` when a run reference is\n159: resolved.\n160: **Format:** Identical to the global `session.json`.\n161: \n162: This file accumulates state incrementally. Its `status` field transitions\n163: from `\"running\"` to `\"completed\"` or `\"failed\"` on the final `finalize`\n164: call.\n165: \n166: ### runs/`<runId>`/events.jsonl (append-only event log)\n167: \n168: **Path:** `.super-ralph/runs/<runId>/events.jsonl`\n169: **Written by:** `src/run-state.ts:recordEvent` — one line appended per event.\n170: **Read by:** `src/run-status.ts` (line count only).\n171: **Format:** One JSON object per line:\n172: `{ \"ts\": \"<ISO 8601>\", \"event\": <EngineEvent> }`.\n173: \n174: This is an append-only log. Each line is written synchronously with\n175: `appendFileSync`. The file is never truncated or rewritten.\n176: \n177: ### runs/`<runId>`/iterations/`<NNN>`-`<label>`.log (transcript)\n178: \n179: **Path:** `.super-ralph/runs/<runId>/iterations/<NNN>-<label>.log`\n180: **Written by:** `src/run-state.ts:writeIterationTranscript` after each\n181: iteration.\n182: **Read by:** Operator; path surfaced by `run-status.ts` as\n183: `latestTranscript`.\n184: **Format:** Plain text with Markdown headings. Contains two sections:\n185: `## Display Stream` (human-readable text) and `## Raw Event Stream` (SSE\n186: lines), present only when the respective buffer is non-empty. The filename\n187: zero-pads the iteration index to three digits and lowercases and\n188: hyphen-separates the label, truncated to 80 characters\n189: (`src/run-state.ts:30–35`).\n190: \n191: ### progress.md (iteration history)\n192: \n193: **Path:** `.super-ralph/progress.md`\n194: **Written by:** `src/progress.ts:appendProgress` after every iteration.\n195: **Read by:** `src/progress.ts:readRecentProgress`, called by\n196: `src/forward.ts` and `src/reverse.ts` in their `nextIteration` callbacks.\n197: **Format:** Append-only Markdown. Each iteration appends one block describing\n198: the outcome, cost, tokens, and files changed.\n199: \n200: This file provides the agent with prior-iteration context. The forward phase\n201: reads the last N entries and injects them into the prompt template.\n202: \n203: ---\n204: \n205: ## External State\n206: \n207: ### BeadInfo (owned by `br` CLI)\n208: \n209: Defined in `src/types.ts:2`. super-ralph reads bead state by spawning\n210: `br` subprocesses and parsing their JSON output. It never reads `.beads/`\n211: files directly.\n212: \n213: | Field | Type | Description |\n214: | --- | --- | --- |\n215: | `id` | `string` | Unique bead identifier |\n216: | `title` | `string` | Short description |\n217: | `description` | `string \\| undefined` | Full task description |\n218: | `status` | `\"open\" \\| \"in_progress\" \\| \"closed\"` | Lifecycle status |\n219: | `labels` | `string[]` | Free-form labels; `area:<name>` prefix used for model routing |\n220: | `priority` | `number` | 0–4 (0 = critical) |\n221: | `dependsOn` | `string[]` | bead IDs that must close before this can start |\n222: | `blocks` | `string[]` | bead IDs that this bead blocks |\n223: | `type` | `string \\| undefined` | `\"epic\"`, `\"task\"`, etc. |\n224: | `parentId` | `string \\| undefined` | ID of the parent epic |\n225: \n226: **Status transitions** (driven by `br` CLI, not by super-ralph directly):\n227: \n228: ```text\n229: \"open\"  →  \"in_progress\"  →  \"closed\"\n230: ```\n231: \n232: The forward phase closes beads by calling `br close <beadId>` via\n233: `src/beads.ts:closeBead`. The `\"in_progress\"` state is set by the `br`\n234: CLI internally.\n235: \n236: ### opencode Session State (owned by opencode server)\n237: \n238: The opencode server maintains its own in-process session store. super-ralph\n239: creates sessions via `client.session.create(...)` and interacts with them\n240: via the SSE stream. Session state is not accessible to super-ralph except\n241: through the SDK methods.\n242: \n243: ---\n244: \n245: ## Module References\n246: \n247: | Module | Role |\n248: | --- | --- |\n249: | [`spec/modules/infrastructure/run-state.md`](../modules/infrastructure/run-state.md) | Writes `SessionState` and all run artifacts |\n250: | [`spec/modules/infrastructure/run-status.md`](../modules/infrastructure/run-status.md) | Reads run artifacts for the `status` command |\n251: | [`spec/modules/infrastructure/progress.md`](../modules/infrastructure/progress.md) | Manages `progress.md` reads and writes |\n252: | [`spec/modules/engine/engine.md`](../modules/engine/engine.md) | Owns engine loop counters and `IterationResult` construction |\n253: | [`spec/modules/infrastructure/types.md`](../modules/infrastructure/types.md) | Defines `BeadInfo`, `IterationResult`, `LoopResult`, `CompletionResult` |\n254: | [`spec/modules/integrations/beads.md`](../modules/integrations/beads.md) | Reads and mutates `BeadInfo` via `br` CLI |\n255: | [`spec/modules/integrations/opencode.md`](../modules/integrations/opencode.md) | Manages `StreamCapture` and `ServerHandle` |\n256: \n257: ## Open Questions\n258: \n259: - The exact behavior when `retryCount` reaches `max_retries` on the same\n260:   label in a subsequent call to the same phase is unconfirmed; the map is\n261:   local to the `runPhaseLoop` call and does not persist. [INFERRED]\n262: - The distinction between `\"stalled\"` and `\"timeout\"` status values is not\n263:   documented in `src/types.ts` comments. [UNKNOWN]\n\n(End of file - total 263 lines)\n</content>","title":"spec/behavior/state-model.md","metadata":{"preview":"# State Model\n\n> Key state entities, their fields, transitions, and the modules that own them.\n\n**Source examined at commit:** `ecc95c0` (2026-02-27)\n\n## Overview\n\nState in super-ralph is partitioned across three scopes:\n\n- **In-process transient state** — lives only for the duration of a single\n  `runPhaseLoop` call and is discarded when the process exits.\n- **On-disk persistent state** — written to the `.super-ralph/` directory\n  and survives process restarts.\n- **External state** — owned by out-of-process services (the opencode server\n  and the `br` CLI); super-ralph reads and mutates it only through typed\n  interfaces.\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1772181458278,"end":1772181458284}}}}
