{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772181563128,"sessionID":"ses_361c37f15ffeuVWV0XN4ZPvLel","part":{"id":"prt_c9e40a4430018yGFRpPKY0eyl0","sessionID":"ses_361c37f15ffeuVWV0XN4ZPvLel","messageID":"msg_c9e409ac7001lb5vDOvOoNpQMC","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_018DnusoxSsSbFEjdx5u8wtJ","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/spec/behavior/error-handling.md","offset":200,"limit":250},"output":"<path>/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/spec/behavior/error-handling.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>200: \n201: ### src/decompose.ts\n202: \n203: | Condition | Error message | Recovery |\n204: | --- | --- | --- |\n205: | `--spec` file not found | `Spec file not found: <path>` | Thrown before loop starts; run aborts; exit code `1` |\n206: \n207: ### src/config.ts\n208: \n209: | Condition | Error message | Recovery |\n210: | --- | --- | --- |\n211: | Model string lacks a `/` separator | `Invalid model format \"<value>\" — expected \"provider/model\"` | Thrown at model resolution time; propagates to iteration catch or aborts run startup |\n212: \n213: ### src/timeout.ts\n214: \n215: | Condition | Error message | Recovery |\n216: | --- | --- | --- |\n217: | Deadline exceeded | Message passed by caller (e.g., `Iteration timed out after 30m`) | Exception caught by engine iteration catch; strategy applied |\n218: \n219: ---\n220: \n221: ## Per-Workflow Negative-Path Scenarios\n222: \n223: ### WF-01: Project Initialization (`super-ralph init`)\n224: \n225: **Scenario: `bun` not on PATH**\n226: \n227: The operator runs `super-ralph init` on a machine where `bun` is not\n228: installed.\n229: \n230: 1. `src/init.ts` reaches the step that runs `bun install` inside `.opencode/`.\n231: 2. The child process spawn fails or exits non-zero.\n232: 3. The error is printed to stderr.\n233: 4. The opencode plugin is not installed; `task_complete` will not be\n234:    registered in subsequent phase runs.\n235: \n236: **Observable outcome:** Error message on stderr. `.opencode/plugins/` is\n237: absent or incomplete. Subsequent `forward`, `decompose`, or `reverse` runs\n238: will always produce `stalled` results because the agent cannot call\n239: `task_complete`.\n240: \n241: **Assumption:** The operator must install `bun` and re-run `super-ralph init`\n242: to recover. [ASSUMED]\n243: \n244: ---\n245: \n246: ### WF-02: Spec Generation (`super-ralph reverse`)\n247: \n248: **Scenario: Agent never calls `task_complete`**\n249: \n250: The operator runs `super-ralph reverse --interactive`. The agent asks\n251: questions and writes a spec, but does not call `task_complete` before the\n252: session goes idle.\n253: \n254: 1. `runPrompt` streams the session until `session.idle` fires\n255:    (`src/opencode.ts:239`).\n256: 2. `extractCompletion` scans session messages and finds no `task_complete`\n257:    tool call.\n258: 3. `CompletionResult` defaults to `{ status: \"stalled\", reason: \"Session\n259:    completed without calling task_complete\" }`.\n260: 4. The engine applies the configured failure strategy.\n261: \n262: **Observable outcome:** Iteration is recorded as `stalled`. With strategy\n263: `retry`, the same session re-runs up to `max_retries` times. With `abort`,\n264: the run exits immediately with code `1`. With `skip`, the loop continues to\n265: the next iteration (or exits if `maxIterations` is reached). [CONFIRMED:\n266: `src/opencode.ts:285–288`, `src/engine.ts:170–203`]\n267: \n268: ---\n269: \n270: ### WF-03: Spec Decomposition (`super-ralph decompose`)\n271: \n272: **Scenario: `br create` fails during epic creation**\n273: \n274: The operator runs `super-ralph decompose --spec docs/specs/foo.md` but the\n275: `br` CLI is not on `PATH`.\n276: \n277: 1. `src/decompose.ts` calls `runBr([\"create\", \"--type\", \"epic\", ...])`.\n278: 2. The spawn fails or exits non-zero.\n279: 3. `runBr` throws `br create --type epic failed (exit N): <stderr>`.\n280: 4. The exception propagates before the loop starts.\n281: 5. The run is finalized as `failed` in the engine's `finally` block.\n282: \n283: **Observable outcome:** Error message on stderr. No epic is created in\n284: `.beads/`. No iterations run. Exit code `1`. [CONFIRMED: `src/beads.ts:16`,\n285: `src/engine.ts:248–252`]\n286: \n287: ---\n288: \n289: ### WF-04: Implementation (`super-ralph forward`)\n290: \n291: **Scenario: Agent times out while implementing a bead**\n292: \n293: The operator runs `super-ralph forward --epic E-001`. During iteration 3,\n294: the agent issues a long-running shell command and produces no SSE output for\n295: longer than `inactivity_timeout_seconds` (default: 180 seconds).\n296: \n297: 1. The inactivity watchdog in `runPrompt` detects that no SSE event has\n298:    arrived in 180 seconds and throws `Session inactive for 180s`.\n299: 2. A best-effort `session.abort()` is called on the opencode session.\n300: 3. The exception propagates out of `runPrompt` and `withTimeout`.\n301: 4. The engine's iteration `catch` block records the iteration as\n302:    `status: \"error\"` with `reason: \"Session inactive for 180s\"`.\n303: 5. The failure strategy is applied. With `retry` (default), the bead is\n304:    retried up to `max_retries` times.\n305: 6. The transcript for the failed iteration is written with whatever output\n306:    was captured before the timeout.\n307: \n308: **Observable outcome:** Error message printed to stdout (via `iteration.error`\n309: event). Bead remains open in `.beads/`. Run continues if strategy is `retry`\n310: or `skip`. With `abort`, the run exits with code `1` and remaining beads are\n311: not processed. [CONFIRMED: `src/opencode.ts:177–178`, `src/engine.ts:208–228`]\n312: \n313: ---\n314: \n315: ### WF-05: Run Status (`super-ralph status`)\n316: \n317: **Scenario: Referenced run ID does not exist**\n318: \n319: The operator runs `super-ralph status --run 1234567890-abc` but no such run\n320: directory exists under `.super-ralph/runs/`.\n321: \n322: 1. `src/run-status.ts:getRunStatus` attempts to resolve the run ID.\n323: 2. No matching directory is found.\n324: 3. An error is thrown and printed to stderr.\n325: \n326: **Observable outcome:** Error on stderr. Exit code `1`. No files are\n327: modified. [CONFIRMED: `src/run-status.ts` — behavior inferred from structure]\n328: \n329: ---\n330: \n331: ### WF-06: Environment Validation (`super-ralph doctor`)\n332: \n333: **Scenario: Broken plugin symlink causes opencode startup failure**\n334: \n335: The operator runs a phase command on a machine where a prior project's\n336: opencode plugin left a dangling symlink in `~/.config/opencode/plugins/`.\n337: \n338: 1. `startServer()` in `src/opencode.ts:75` calls\n339:    `checkBrokenSymlinks({ fix: true })` before spawning the server.\n340: 2. The broken symlink is detected and removed automatically.\n341: 3. A message is printed: `Fixed N broken symlink(s) in ~/.config/opencode/`.\n342: 4. Server startup proceeds normally.\n343: \n344: **Observable outcome:** Broken symlinks are repaired transparently. The\n345: operator may notice the `Fixed N broken symlink(s)` message but the run is\n346: not interrupted. [CONFIRMED: `src/opencode.ts:74–78`]\n347: \n348: **Scenario: `super-ralph doctor` finds broken symlink without `--fix`**\n349: \n350: 1. `doctor` runs `checkBrokenSymlinks({ fix: false })`.\n351: 2. The broken path is added to the `broken` array.\n352: 3. The check is printed as failed.\n353: 4. Exit code `1`.\n354: \n355: The operator must re-run `super-ralph doctor --fix` or manually remove the\n356: symlink to repair the environment. [CONFIRMED: `src/opencode.ts:31–69`]\n357: \n358: ---\n359: \n360: ### WF-07: Agent Completion Signaling (`task_complete` tool)\n361: \n362: **Scenario: Plugin not installed**\n363: \n364: The operator initializes a project but the `bun install` step during init\n365: failed, leaving `.opencode/plugins/super-ralph.js` absent.\n366: \n367: 1. The opencode server starts successfully.\n368: 2. The agent receives the prompt and executes normally.\n369: 3. The agent attempts to call `task_complete` but the tool is not registered.\n370: 4. The agent either errors on the tool call or completes the session without\n371:    signaling.\n372: 5. `extractCompletion` finds no `task_complete` call in session messages.\n373: 6. Result defaults to `stalled`.\n374: 7. The failure strategy is applied.\n375: \n376: **Observable outcome:** Every iteration stalls. With `retry` strategy and\n377: default `max_retries: 3`, each item is attempted four times before being\n378: skipped. The run exits with exit code `1` after all items are exhausted or\n379: the iteration limit is reached. [CONFIRMED: `src/opencode.ts:285–288`]\n380: \n381: ---\n382: \n383: ## Resilience Summary\n384: \n385: | Mechanism | Scope | Default value | Behavior |\n386: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n387: | `engine.strategy = \"retry\"` | Per-iteration failure | `retry` | Re-run up to `max_retries` times |\n388: | `engine.max_retries` | Per-iteration failure | `3` | Retry limit before fallback to skip |\n389: | `engine.timeout_minutes` | Per-iteration | `30` minutes | Hard wall-clock timeout; kills session |\n390: | `engine.inactivity_timeout_seconds` | Per-session | `180` seconds | No-event watchdog; aborts session |\n391: | `checkBrokenSymlinks({ fix: true })` | Server startup | Always | Auto-repairs broken plugin symlinks |\n392: | `finally` block in `runPhaseLoop` | Run lifetime | Always | Ensures run is finalized and server is closed |\n393: | Best-effort `session.abort()` | Inactivity timeout | Always | Prevents orphaned API sessions |\n394: | SSE stream `stream.return()` | Per-session cleanup | Always | Closes SSE connection to unblock process exit |\n395: \n396: ---\n397: \n398: ## Open Questions\n399: \n400: - Whether the agent's `task_complete({ status: \"failed\" })` call is\n401:   distinguished from `stalled` in the operator-visible event log is not\n402:   fully confirmed; both result in the failure strategy being applied.\n403:   [UNKNOWN]\n404: - The exact error surfaced when the opencode API provider rejects a prompt\n405:   (for example, due to a rate limit or invalid credentials) is not\n406:   characterized; it likely manifests as a `session.error` SSE event but\n407:   the exact message format is unconfirmed. [UNKNOWN]\n408: - Whether `session.abort()` always prevents further token consumption after\n409:   an inactivity timeout depends on opencode server behavior, which is\n410:   outside the scope of this codebase. [ASSUMED]\n411: - The behavior when `engine.max_retries` is set to `0` is unconfirmed;\n412:   the condition `currentRetries < max_retries` would be false on the first\n413:   attempt, causing immediate fallback to `skip`. [INFERRED: `src/engine.ts:173`]\n414: - The `session.error` SSE event is captured and breaks out of the streaming\n415:   loop (`src/opencode.ts:246–263`), but it is not clear whether it is\n416:   recorded as a distinct `CompletionResult` status or falls through to the\n417:   default `stalled` result. [UNKNOWN]\n\n(End of file - total 417 lines)\n</content>","title":"spec/behavior/error-handling.md","metadata":{"preview":"\n### src/decompose.ts\n\n| Condition | Error message | Recovery |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `--spec` file not found | `Spec file not found: <path>` | Thrown before loop starts; run aborts; exit code `1` |\n\n### src/config.ts\n\n| Condition | Error message | Recovery |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Model string lacks a `/` separator | `Invalid model format \"<value>\" — expected \"provider/model\"` | Thrown at model resolution time; propagates to iteration catch or aborts run startup |\n\n### src/timeout.ts\n\n| Condition | Error message | Recovery |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Deadline exceeded | Message passed by caller (e.g., `Iteration timed out after 30m`) | Exception caught by engine iteration catch; strategy applied |\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1772181563122,"end":1772181563127}}}}
