      "errorMessage": "task_id: ses_361c35b27ffeGTeeu2PuQElm2b (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a comprehensive picture of the entire codebase. Here is the complete report:\n\n---\n\n## Project Structure Overview\n\n**Project name:** `super-ralph` (package name), described as \"A unified SDLC framework for AI-assisted software development.\"\n\n**Runtime:** Bun (TypeScript, ESM). Built with `bun build`. Binary: `super-ralph`.\n\n**Top-level directories:**\n\n```\nagent-framework/\n  src/           — 19 TypeScript source modules\n  spec/          — Reverse-engineered specifications (architecture, behavior, module docs, workflows)\n  docs/          — Historical design plans and reference docs\n  tests/         — E2E shell scripts and unit test fixtures\n  templates/     — Default Handlebars prompt templates and config scaffold\n  skills/        — Built-in skill Markdown files (question banks for reverse phase)\n  tasks/         — Per-project generated PRD/spec output (runtime)\n  dist/          — Compiled output\n  .super-ralph/  — Per-project runtime state (config, run artifacts, progress log)\n  .opencode/     — opencode plugin (task_complete tool registration)\n  .beads/        — Beads task tracker state (managed by br CLI)\n  .vale/         — Vale prose linting configuration and vocabulary\n  .markdownlint.json — Markdownlint configuration\n  .vale.ini      — Vale configuration\n  AGENTS.md      — Agent instructions\n  README.md      — Full user documentation\n  package.json   — Project manifest\n  tsconfig.json  — TypeScript config\n```\n\n**Key source modules (`src/`):**\n\n| Module | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `index.ts` | CLI entry point — argument parsing and dispatch |\n| `engine.ts` | Core Ralph loop: select, prompt, execute, evaluate |\n| `forward.ts` | Forward phase: beads -> code |\n| `decompose.ts` | Decompose phase: spec -> beads |\n| `reverse.ts` | Reverse phase: input -> spec |\n| `opencode.ts` | opencode server lifecycle, SSE streaming, result extraction |\n| `interactive.ts` | Interactive reverse mode: question/answer via @clack/prompts |\n| `beads.ts` | Thin wrapper around `br` CLI, returns typed `BeadInfo` |\n| `config.ts` | Loads and merges `.super-ralph/config.toml` with defaults |\n| `template.ts` | Loads and renders Handlebars `.hbs` prompt templates |\n| `events.ts` | Engine event union type, pub/sub emitter, default console renderer |\n| `run-state.ts` | Persists per-run artifacts: session.json, events.jsonl, transcripts |\n| `run-status.ts` | Read-only companion: resolves run references and reads artifacts |\n| `progress.ts` | Appends and reads Markdown iteration progress summaries |\n| `output-parser.ts` | `StreamCapture` class — accumulates raw/display SSE output, capped at 250k chars |\n| `timeout.ts` | `withTimeout()` — races a Promise against a deadline |\n| `skills.ts` | Resolves skill names to Markdown question-bank content |\n| `init.ts` | Scaffolds new project: directories, templates, opencode plugin, br init |\n| `types.ts` | Central type definitions — all shared interfaces |\n\n**Dependencies (from `package.json`):**\n\n- `@clack/prompts` — interactive terminal prompts (interactive reverse mode)\n- `@iarna/toml` — TOML config parsing\n- `@opencode-ai/sdk` — opencode AI coding agent SDK (v1 + v2)\n- `handlebars` — prompt template rendering\n\n---\n\n## Error Classes and Types\n\nNo custom `Error` subclasses are defined. All errors are plain `new Error(message)`. Error *types* are encoded as string literal union values in the type system.\n\n**`CompletionResult.status`** (`src/types.ts:64`) — the primary agent-signal error taxonomy:\n\n| Value | Meaning |\n|---|---|\n| `\"complete\"` | Agent signalled iteration done; loop continues |\n| `\"phase_done\"` | Agent signalled all phase work done; loop exits |\n| `\"blocked\"` | Bead has unresolved dependencies; iteration is skipped |\n| `\"failed\"` | Agent explicitly reported failure |\n| `\"stalled\"` | Session ended without calling `task_complete` (default fallback in `extractCompletion`) |\n| `\"timeout\"` | Wall-clock deadline exceeded (set by `withTimeout`) |\n| `\"error\"` | Exception thrown inside the iteration try-block |\n\n**`IterationResult.status`** (`src/types.ts:52`) — same union, used in per-iteration records.\n\n**`SessionState.status`** (`src/run-state.ts:14`) — run-level lifecycle:\n\n| Value | Meaning |\n|---|---|\n| `\"running\"` | Run in progress |\n| `\"completed\"` | Run finalized successfully (`failed == 0`) |\n| `\"failed\"` | Run finalized with failures or an uncaught exception |\n\n**`ErrorStrategy`** (`src/types.ts:103`) — the three engine-level failure handling modes:\n\n```typescript\ntype ErrorStrategy = \"retry\" | \"skip\" | \"abort\";\n```\n\n**`BeadInfo.status`** (`src/types.ts:6`):\n\n```typescript\nstatus: \"open\" | \"in_progress\" | \"closed\"\n```\n\n**Thrown errors found in source code:**\n\n- `new Error(\"Failed to create session\")` — `src/opencode.ts:126`\n- `new Error(\"OpenCode server started but not responding: ...\")` — `src/opencode.ts:87`\n- `new Error(\"Cannot connect to OpenCode server at ${url}: ...\")` — `src/opencode.ts:106`\n- `new Error(\"Session inactive for Ns\")` — `src/opencode.ts:178` (inactivity watchdog)\n- `new Error(\"br ${args} failed (exit N): ${stderr}\")` — `src/beads.ts:16`\n- `new Error(\"Spec file not found: ${flags.specPath}\")` — `src/decompose.ts:17`\n- `new Error(\"Invalid model format '...' — expected 'provider/model'\")` — `src/config.ts:120`\n- `new Error(errorMessage)` — `src/timeout.ts:10` (generic timeout rejection)\n\n---\n\n## Retry / Recovery / Abort Patterns\n\nThe engine (`src/engine.ts`) implements three configurable failure strategies, selected by `config.engine.strategy`:\n\n### 1. `\"retry\"` (default)\n\nWhen an iteration resolves to any failure status (`failed`, `stalled`, `timeout`, `error`), if `retryCount.get(label) < config.engine.max_retries` (default: 3):\n\n- `retryCount` is incremented for that `iterationLabel`.\n- `iteration--` decrements the loop counter, causing the same work item to be selected again on the next pass.\n- `iteration.retrying` event is emitted with attempt/maxRetries.\n\nWhen retry count is exhausted, falls through to `skip` behavior.\n\n### 2. `\"abort\"`\n\nOn any failure status (or when retries are exhausted):\n\n- `failed` counter incremented.\n- `iteration.failed` event emitted with `action: \"aborting\"`.\n- `break` exits the loop immediately.\n- Run is finalized as `\"failed\"`.\n\n### 3. `\"skip\"` (also the retry-exhausted fallback)\n\nOn any failure status:\n\n- `failed` counter incremented.\n- `iteration.failed` event emitted with `action: \"skipping\"`.\n- Loop continues to next iteration.\n\n### Additional recovery patterns\n\n**Inactivity watchdog** (`src/opencode.ts`): A polling loop races `iterator.next()` against a 10-second tick timer. If no SSE event has arrived within `inactivityTimeoutMs` (default 180s), throws `\"Session inactive for Ns\"`. Best-effort `session.abort()` is called before re-throwing, to prevent zombie sessions.\n\n**Hard wall-clock timeout** (`src/engine.ts:117`): `withTimeout(runPrompt(...), timeoutMs)` wraps every prompt call. Timeout rejects with a descriptive error; the catch block in the iteration try/catch catches it and applies the error strategy.\n\n**Uncaught exception in iteration** (`src/engine.ts:208`): Any exception thrown inside the iteration's try block is caught, recorded as an `\"error\"` status `IterationResult`, and the error strategy is applied. If strategy is `abort`, the loop breaks.\n\n**Uncaught exception outside iterations** (`src/engine.ts:248–253`): The `finally` block always calls `runTracker.finalize(\"failed\")` if the run was not already finalized, and calls `cleanup()` (server close + listener detach).\n\n**Session abort on timeout** (`src/reverse.ts:119`): Interactive reverse mode also wraps its session in `withTimeout`, and if it times out, calls `v2Client.session.abort()` in a best-effort try/catch before re-throwing.\n\n**Broken symlink auto-repair** (`src/opencode.ts:75`): `startServer()` always calls `checkBrokenSymlinks({ fix: true })` before spawning the opencode server, automatically removing broken plugin symlinks that would crash it.\n\n---\n\n## Core Workflows\n\nThe framework implements the \"Ralph Loop\": **SELECT → PROMPT → EXECUTE → EVALUATE**, repeated across three composable phases:\n\n### Phase 1: `reverse` — Input → Spec\n\nTwo sub-modes:\n\n- **Interactive** (no inputs or `--interactive`): spawns an opencode session, intercepts `question.asked` SSE events, renders questions via `@clack/prompts`, sends answers back. Agent writes a Markdown spec file and calls `task_complete({ status: \"phase_done\" })`.\n- **Autonomous** (with positional inputs): runs the engine loop (max 20 iterations). Each iteration renders `reverse.hbs` with inputs + current spec content for refinement. Continues until agent signals `phase_done`.\n- **Mixed** (inputs + `--interactive`): inputs used as context, interactive Q&A flow still used.\n\n### Phase 2: `decompose` — Spec → Beads\n\n- Creates an epic via `br create --type epic`.\n- Runs the engine loop (max 50 iterations).\n- Each iteration: renders `decompose.hbs` with spec content + existing beads. Agent creates one or more beads via `br create`.\n- Continues until agent signals `phase_done` (all spec requirements covered).\n- Optionally appends review, bugscan, and audit beads post-loop.\n\n### Phase 3: `forward` — Beads → Code\n\n- Queries `br ready --parent <epicId>` to get unblocked ready beads.\n- Runs the engine loop (max: `beads.length * 2` iterations).\n- Each iteration: selects the highest-priority ready bead, fetches its details, reads recent progress, renders `forward.hbs`, resolves model by area label.\n- Agent implements the bead, runs quality gates (`bun run typecheck`), commits, closes the bead, calls `task_complete`.\n- Loop exits when `br ready` returns no beads (`nextIteration` returns `null`).\n\n### Engine Loop (shared by all three phases)\n\n```\n1. load config\n2. callbacks.setup() → maxIterations, description\n3. startRunTracker() → creates run directory, session.json\n4. startServer() or connectToServer()\n5. while iteration < maxIterations:\n   a. callbacks.nextIteration() → PhaseIteration | null\n      (null → exit loop)\n   b. createSession()\n   c. withTimeout(runPrompt(), timeout_minutes)\n      - SSE stream: text deltas to stdout, tool statuses\n      - session.idle → read session.messages() for task_complete\n      - inactivity watchdog fires every 10s\n   d. writeIterationTranscript()\n   e. appendProgress()\n   f. callbacks.handleResult() → continue bool\n   g. apply error strategy (retry/skip/abort)\n   h. sleep(iteration_delay_ms)\n6. emit loop.completed\n7. runTracker.finalize()\n8. finally: server.close(), detach listeners\n```\n\n### Completion Signaling (agent → orchestrator)\n\nThe agent calls the `task_complete` tool registered by `.opencode/plugins/super-ralph.js`. After `session.idle`, `runPrompt` scans `session.messages()` for a `task_complete` tool-call result. The four valid statuses:\n\n- `complete` — iteration done, continue loop\n- `phase_done` — all work done, exit loop\n- `blocked` — skip this item, continue\n- `failed` — failure, apply error strategy\n\nIf no `task_complete` call is found, the result defaults to `stalled`.\n\n---\n\n## spec/ Directory Contents\n\nThe `spec/` directory contains reverse-engineered specifications (produced from source code, not from author design documents). Current state as of commit `ecc95c0` (2026-02-27):\n\n**Meta documents:**\n- `spec/README.md` — Navigation guide, artifact table (all module specs currently listed as \"pending\")\n- `spec/CONVENTIONS.md` — Writing rules: clean-room constraints, confidence labels (`[CONFIRMED]`, `[INFERRED]`, `[ASSUMED]`, `[UNKNOWN]`), required section template, markdown style rules, file naming rules\n\n**Architecture docs:**\n- `spec/architecture/overview.md` — Full domain map: 5 domains (CLI, Phases, Engine, Integrations, Infrastructure), all cross-domain interaction boundaries, filesystem layout\n- `spec/architecture/runtime-lifecycle.md` — Detailed 3-stage lifecycle (Initialization, Steady-state loop, Shutdown) with sequence diagram; configuration values governing lifecycle; `super-ralph init` sequence\n\n**Behavior docs:**\n- `spec/behavior/configuration.md` — 3-tier config precedence (CLI flags > config.toml > defaults), full default table, merge semantics, model resolution, validation behavior, environment variables\n- `spec/behavior/persistence-and-io.md` — All filesystem read/write boundaries (by lifecycle stage), network I/O table, child process table, stdout/stderr/stdin usage, process exit codes, I/O ordering guarantees\n- `spec/behavior/state-model.md` — In-process transient state (`SessionState`, engine loop counters, `IterationResult`, `StreamCapture`, `ServerHandle`), on-disk persistent state (all file formats), external state (`BeadInfo`, opencode session)\n\n**Workflow docs:**\n- `spec/workflows/core-workflows.md` — 7 workflows: WF-01 init, WF-02 reverse, WF-03 decompose, WF-04 forward, WF-05 status, WF-06 doctor, WF-07 task_complete signaling. Each includes triggers, preconditions, normal flow, alternate flows, failure outcomes, observable outputs.\n\n**Module docs** (`spec/modules/` — all fully written):\n- `spec/modules/cli/index.md` — CLI entry point module spec\n- `spec/modules/engine/engine.md` — Engine module spec (failure modes, retry/skip/abort)\n- `spec/modules/infrastructure/` — config, events, init, output-parser, progress, run-state, run-status, skills, template, timeout, types\n- `spec/modules/integrations/` — beads, interactive, opencode\n- `spec/modules/phases/` — forward, decompose, reverse\n\n**Note:** `spec/README.md`'s artifact table still shows all module specs as \"pending\" — this table is outdated; the module spec files do exist and are complete.\n\n---\n\n## Linting Configuration Files\n\n### `.markdownlint.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"default\": true,\n  \"MD013\": {\n    \"line_length\": 80,\n    \"tables\": false,\n    \"code_blocks\": false\n  },\n  \"MD024\": {\n    \"siblings_only\": true\n  }\n}\n```\n\nAll rules enabled by default. Line length enforced at 80 characters (tables and code blocks exempt). Duplicate headings allowed only for siblings (not same level across the document).\n\n### `.vale.ini`\n\n```ini\nStylesPath = .vale/styles\nMinAlertLevel = suggestion\nVocab = spec\n\n[*.md]\nBasedOnStyles = Vale\n```\n\nUses the built-in Vale style, applied to all `.md` files. Minimum alert level: suggestion. Custom vocabulary stored in `.vale/styles/config/vocabularies/spec/accept.txt`.\n\n### `.vale/styles/config/vocabularies/spec/accept.txt`\n\nContains 77 accepted terms including: `BeadInfo`, `LoopConfig`, `LoopResult`, `IterationResult`, `CompletionResult`, `PhaseCallbacks`, `PhaseIteration`, `PromptResult`, `ServerHandle`, `RunTracker`, `StreamCapture`, `OpencodeClient`, `SSE`, `opencode`, `super-ralph`, `br`, `hbs`, `TOML`, `JSONL`, `task_complete`, `stdout`, `stderr`, `stdin`, `runId`, `ForwardFlags`, `DecomposeFlags`, `ReverseFlags`, `PhaseFlags`, `ErrorStrategy`, `EngineEvent`, `EngineEventEmitter`, `EngineEventListener`, `createOpencode`, `promptAsync`, `Handlebars`, `bugscan`, `idempotent`, and others.\n</task_result>",
